= Campaigning

Whether or not we are in an electoral campaign, the party is constantly producing new flyers and handouts. Who should we focus our campaign efforts on?

- @workers: The working class, our traditional base.
- @rural: The "old middle class" of small business owners and independent farmers.
- @unemployed: The unemployed.
- @youth: Students and the broader youth.
- @capitalists: The property owning capitalist class.
- @root: We either don't want to or cannot campaign right now.
- @easy_discard

@workers
subtitle: -1 resources
choose-if: resources >= 1

The workers can no longer be said to consist of a single social unit (if this was ever the case), the capitalist division of labour has created a series of sub-strata. 

Who should we chiefly focus on?

- @tenants: The workers who rent their homes.
- @public: Public sector workers, who have felt neglected by us in the past.
- @private: Private sector workers, the backbone of the workers movement.
- @homeowners: The "new middle class" of homeowning workers.

