The tiny class of capitalists constitutes barely 2% of society. By focussing our campaign on the superiority of private property relations and the ascession into the EEC, we can begin to repair relations with this social group.

Given that fighting the interests of this class constitutes the core of our identity, much of our membership simply refuses to take part in this campaign. Nonetheless, we do notice the relations with some of the bourgeois parties improve.